                    <title>I make sure to have the wikip…</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:Comment:2419"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2011-11-28:6456126:Comment:2419</id>
                                        <updated>2011-11-28T23:03:14.340Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>corey haines</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/128952ghvkcvj</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;I make sure to have the wikipedia page open on a projector, generally to the rules. I find that most people have memorized the rules by the third session, so I usually scroll the page down to some of the example patterns (block, blinker, etc).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is internet access at the venue, then I see people occasionally jumping to the wikipedia page on their own computer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the great things about GoL is that the rules are simple enough to memorize with just a little of time…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                                            <content type="html">
                            &lt;p&gt;I make sure to have the wikipedia page open on a projector, generally to the rules. I find that most people have memorized the rules by the third session, so I usually scroll the page down to some of the example patterns (block, blinker, etc).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If there is internet access at the venue, then I see people occasionally jumping to the wikipedia page on their own computer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the great things about GoL is that the rules are simple enough to memorize with just a little of time thinking about them.&lt;/p&gt;                        </content>
                    
